cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper discusses resource allocation and scheduling in D2D enabled cellular networks, which involves topics related to network protocols, wireless communication, and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper proposes a centralized and distributed algorithm for resource allocation, which involves information theory and system optimization, making cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses energy efficiency, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and security and privacy (cs.CR) in wireless networks.
